			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Default" border="0" />
				<strong>Mob positioning????</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#000000" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>With rogue and pet class in group how many attackers can be at mobs back and rogue still backstab?  I try to move the mob so that the pets are at its back as well as rogue.  Sometimes it is hard to reposition a mob if you have a beastlord in group.  I find that when I try to step back the mob will sit there and attack the beastlord.  I am assuming this is because they don't turn off pet taunt.  But I'm not sure.  I'll have to ask them to turn it off next time to make sure.  What I don't like is when we have no rogue or pet class and all the melee are on the same side as me taking reposte damage.  I never stand in front of a mob when off tanking.  I am in back or to the side if a rogue is present. How lame do you have to be.  I'm just hoping they are not ignorant and only want to improve on thier defense skill.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
