			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Any number of people of pet/people can be hitting a mobs back, as long as the mobs hit box can fit that many people in the back arc of the mob.  For xp groups hiting the back should be easy peasy.<br />
<br />
Basically what I do for positioning.<br />
<br />
Pull past pets so they attack back, most rogues are adpeted enough to get to the back of the mob themselves.  I try not to corner pin a mob (IE having a mob back to a corner) unless I absolutely cannot get it out of there.<br />
<br />
If there is a ranger in the group I ask if the have archery AAs.  If they do, I try and position the mob away from walls, casue walled mobs cause arrows to poof.  Generally this can be hard if there are 3+ pets (so much push and im so lazy =P).</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
