		<!-- message -->
		<div>Assit Puller key.<br />
Center myself in area or room.<br />
Cast CD on Mob continue to cast until the mob comes to you, if the group is stopping it from reaching you then the problem lies with them, usually 3 to 4 CD will make any MOB head your way even from Slows!<br />
<br />
Lock Aggro various ways all fairly easy (chain CD + Voice of Terris+decent DPS as an example)<br />
<br />
I position the mob as close to center of the room pull  area as possible and let everyone push him from one side especially BL warders which appear to be the mellee pushmiesters! <br />
<br />
Rouges of course have to spin with the mob as it gets turned around you but it seems to work very well for me. I just let the mob slip to my right if hes getting pushed from the left and if I have aggro locked turn to face him and he will run into me only to be pushed to the right of my screen again, etc, etc, etc.<br />
<br />
This works well even if everyone starts attacking from different sides you wil notice the mob being pushed in one particular direction, just side step and let it drift that way, turn and repeat.<br />
<br />
BL gaining aggro I see often but if he does he doesnt gain it for long before I capture it again.<br />
<br />
This seems to work well for me against summoning mobs as well especially if I get their attention to the center of the area on the first CD cast if the group screws up and engages it to early then  chain CD it, youll get summoned about three or four times. Just keep slowly walking it back an it will eventually just follow you to center of room/pull area. (IMPORTANT NOTE HERE:if the group walls the mob I dont recommend trying this! I have been summoned into walls and would have ended our raid if it were not for mages and CoTH to get me out)<br />
<br />
I havent had much luck using a guild tanks method but I have seen him postion a mob to the center by beating on it lossing its aggro momentarily then sitting down were he wanted the mob to come to, works very well for him.<br />
<br />
In short after you have managed to position yourself and the mob so that it circles you and the group starts to follow it as it spins around you they will all just seem to fall into line.<br />
<br />
Everytime I have taken the time to try and expalin it it just becomes a mess best just to make it happen and before you know it everyone will follow suite! <br />
<br />
For those special toons that must have the aggro let em have it! After a PoP mob has beat on them for a short period they will quit or die or the cleric will /tell them with a WTF? shortly their after! (Btw how humilitating is it to be killed by a rainbow colored frog thats no larger than the noob rats!)<br />
<br />
My 2cp<br />
<br />
Grave Lord Stihlbohrn<br />
Soulbound of Mith Marr<br />
Ohana!</div>
